{
  "text": "Serial tissue sections are typically mounted to glass slides at random locations and orientations. To facilitate full tissue registration, we first pre-align each tissue section to a reference section based on their contour principal axes [CITATION_1] . Registration is computed between each sequential pair of images within the volume. Low resolution serial images are first converted to grayscale and recognized for tissue components with adaptive global thresholding. We denote the tissue contours as C = {x i = (x i1 , x i2 ) T , ∀i}. With detected C, we next compute the centroid, µ ∈ R 2 , and construct the scatter ma-",
